author: James Wilkinson For Dailymail.Com
title: Fears grow for missing OSU student after body is found | Daily Mail Online
text: Ohio State University student, 21, is shot dead and left near a public park just a day after she failed to return home from work and her car was reported missing Psychology student Reagan Tokes was last seen leaving work at 9:45pm Wed On Thursday afternoon her body was found outside Scioto Grove Metro Park She had been shot. Her car, a 1999 silver Acura, license FGR 8547, is missing It's not known if she was shot in the park, or whether her body was dumped there Police, waiting on coroner, have still not officially linked the park body to Tokes But her death was confirmed by her uncle, and her car was linked to the body Published: 04:04 GMT, 10 February 2017 | Updated: 08:14 GMT, 10 February 2017 35 shares
